---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Privacy Policy - Flashtools"
	description="Flashtools privacy policy. Your images never leave your device — all conversion happens locally in your browser."
	canonicalPath="/privacy"
>
	<Header />

	<main class="legal-layout">
		<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
		<p class="updated">Last updated: July 16, 2026</p>

		<section>
			<h2>Your images stay on your device</h2>
			<p>
				Flashtools converts PNG images to WebP entirely inside your web browser using the
				HTML5 Canvas API. Your files are never uploaded, transmitted, or stored on any
				server. The conversion works even if you disconnect from the internet after the
				page has loaded.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>What we collect</h2>
			<p>
				Almost nothing. Flashtools has no user accounts, no cookies, no advertising, and no
				third-party trackers. To understand whether the tool is useful, we count three
				anonymous events on our own server: a page was viewed, a file was converted, and a
				result was downloaded. Each count stores only the event type and the hour it
				happened. We store no IP address, no browser fingerprint, no identifier of any
				kind, and no information about your files — not their names, contents, sizes, or
				anything else. These counts cannot be traced to a person, and we honor your
				browser's <em>Do Not Track</em> setting by not sending them at all. Our web server
				does not write or retain access logs.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Third-party resources and delivery</h2>
			<p>
				All assets — including fonts — are served from flashtools.app itself; the page
				loads no third-party scripts, fonts, or trackers. The site is delivered through
				<a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Cloudflare</a>,
				which provides DNS, security, and content-delivery services for flashtools.app.
				Like any network provider, Cloudflare may process standard connection data (such
				as your IP address) in transit in order to deliver and protect the service; we do
				not receive or store that data ourselves.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Contact</h2>
			<p>
				Questions about this policy? Open an issue on the project repository or contact the
				site operator.
			</p>
		</section>

		<p><a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; Back to converter</a></p>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.legal-layout {
		flex-grow: 1;
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 760px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 3rem 2rem 5rem 2rem;
		box-sizing: border-box;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		z-index: 10;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: 2.25rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	.updated {
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: var(--color-text-dim);
	}

	section {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.5rem;
	}

	h2 {
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	p {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		line-height: 1.7;
	}

	a {
		color: var(--color-primary);
	}

	.back-link {
		text-decoration: none;
		font-weight: 500;
	}
</style>
